# Dataset_ARR publication: tracked, except large/private artifacts.
# - raw subtrees hold 5 GB of platform exports + ZJS PDFs/source — ship via HF + Zenodo, not git
# - .grader_map.json is the private grader-anonymization key — never commit
# - ZJS variant trees (source_strict/, source_optimistic/) stay local until
#   legal picks one for release; only the chosen variant ships, via HF + Zenodo
#
# Note: blanket-ignoring `data/raw/` is wrong here — once a directory is
# ignored, files inside cannot be re-included via `!file/path`. So instead
# we ignore the specific heavy subtrees and the IP-clearance map files stay
# tracked by default.
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/zjs/source/
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/zjs/source_strict/
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/zjs/source_optimistic/
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/zjs/ZJS Fälle-tasks-*.json
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/zjs/zjs_merged*.json
# IP-clearance roster CSV carries the outreach email column (396 work emails).
# It is the input that produces ip_clearance.json (public, email-free); the
# CSV itself never ships. The roster is regenerated on demand from the
# upstream tracking sheet, not from this file.
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/zjs/ip_clearance_*.csv
# Scripts that hold real grader identities (name → uuid → email) for the
# one-shot anonymization + sample-building pipeline. Outputs are tracked and
# fully anonymized; the scripts themselves stay local until refactored to
# load identities from an external private file.
publications/Dataset_ARR/scripts/anonymize_graders.py
publications/Dataset_ARR/scripts/build_human_grading_sample.py
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/benchathon/
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/grundprinzipien/
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/mock/
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/raw/archive/
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/.grader_map.json
publications/Dataset_ARR/.quarto/
publications/Dataset_ARR/manuscript_files/
publications/Dataset_ARR/manuscript.tex
publications/Dataset_ARR/manuscript.fdb_latexmk

# The repo-wide `*.json` rule below hides every JSON in the project. The
# Dataset_ARR publication needs its small derived JSONs tracked (the ones
# the manuscript loads), so unignore them explicitly.
# Note: the IP-clearance roster (CSV with emails AND its email-free JSON
# derivative) stays out of the public repo — it's internal accounting and
# the redaction state is already encoded in source_strict/.
!publications/Dataset_ARR/data/interim/*.json
!publications/Dataset_ARR/data/processed/*.json
# …but re-block all merged ZJS dumps. The unredacted `zjs.json` is the
# full-text 21 MB merge (never publish); the strict and optimistic variants
# are computed from raw/, ship only to HF/Zenodo at release time, and are
# regenerable from `scripts/zjs_apply_ip_clearance.py`. Keeping them out of
# git defers the strict-vs-optimistic legal choice to release time.
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/interim/zjs.json
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/interim/zjs_strict.json
publications/Dataset_ARR/data/interim/zjs_optimistic.json
